# Lesson 1-4 — Congruence Criteria (SSS, SAS, ASA, AAS, HL)

## Today's Goals

* Identify and apply the five triangle congruence criteria
* Determine whether two triangles are congruent based on given information
* Distinguish between valid and invalid congruence shortcuts

---

## Vocabulary

* **congruent triangles** — triangles with the same size and shape; all corresponding sides and angles are equal
* **SSS (Side-Side-Side)** — three pairs of corresponding sides are congruent
* **SAS (Side-Angle-Side)** — two pairs of sides and the included angle are congruent
* **ASA (Angle-Side-Angle)** — two pairs of angles and the included side are congruent
* **AAS (Angle-Angle-Side)** — two pairs of angles and a non-included side are congruent
* **HL (Hypotenuse-Leg)** — right triangles with congruent hypotenuses and one pair of congruent legs
* **included angle** — the angle formed between two sides
* **included side** — the side between two angles

---

