## Example 5 — HL Congruence (Right Triangles)

Right triangle ABC has hypotenuse AB = 13 and leg BC = 5. Right triangle DEF has hypotenuse DE = 13 and leg EF = 5. Are the triangles congruent?

### Step 1: Confirm Both Are Right Triangles

∠C = 90° in △ABC and ∠F = 90° in △DEF.

### Step 2: Identify Corresponding Parts

| △ABC | △DEF | Relationship |
|------|------|-------------|
| AB = 13 (hyp.) | DE = 13 (hyp.) | AB ≅ DE |
| BC = 5 (leg) | EF = 5 (leg) | BC ≅ EF |
| ∠C = 90° | ∠F = 90° | ∠C ≅ ∠F |

### Step 3: Apply HL

The hypotenuses are congruent and one pair of legs are congruent. Both triangles are right triangles.

By **HL**, △ABC ≅ △DEF.

✅ Answer: Yes — the right triangles are congruent by HL.

